  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a cataplana vessel over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced guanciale and cook until crispy, then set aside.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the toasted buckwheat and cook for 2 minutes, until lightly toasted.",
    "Add the lemon zest, lemon juice, canned tomatoes, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the cooked guanciale back into the vessel and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, until the buckwheat is tender.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
